Colombian Stocks: Colinversiones, Ecopetrol, Pacific Rubiales

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-02-23T21:16:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/colombian-stocks-colinversiones-ecopetrol-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index increased 2.2 percent to 14,602.91, while
the Colcap Index gained 2.2 percent to 1,698.63.  Cia. Colombiana de Inversiones SA (COLINV CB) surged 8.3
percent to 5,110 pesos, the biggest jump since October 2009. The
electricity holding company known as Colinversiones said it
posted net income in 2010 of 258.5 billion pesos, according to a
statement late yesterday on the website of Colombia’s financial
regulator.  Oil producers climbed after touched $100 a barrel as
Libya’s violent uprising threatened to disrupt exports from
Africa’s third-biggest supplier and spread to other crude-
producing nations in the Middle East.    Ecopetrol SA  (ECOPETL CB), the state-controlled  oil
company , jumped 3.7 percent to 3,900 pesos.    Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp . (PREC CB), the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, advanced 3.1
percent to 61,680 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  